<id>http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=5779&amp;p=25591#p25591</id>
<link href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=5779&amp;p=25591#p25591"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[[Animated Start Button]   Spore Rotate &amp; Spore Rotate Tinted]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=5779&amp;p=25591#p25591"><![CDATA[
[Animated Start Button] Spore Rotate<br /><br />The spokes rotate a bit, less than a second in length.<br /><br />With limited knowledge, and software, I used basic ways to rotate the spokes. <br />Took a while to figure it all out. <br />Separated the spokes from the background, <br />so it can be rotated separately on a new layer in image program.<br /><br />Next, it's all math.<br />It has 5 spokes for 360 degrees.<br />To rotate a spoke to next position equals 72 degrees.<br />To get smooth movement, made it rotate 6 degrees each time.<br />So 12 times is where one spoke got to next spoke position, 1/5 rotation.<br />I duplicated those frames again to get total of 2/5 rotation.<br /><br />If user hovers, &amp; aborts menu, spokes rotate backwards to a little bounce at endd. <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_e_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /><br /><br />On Win 10, I have button size at 42<br /><br /><br />and<br />[Animated Start Button] Spore Rotate Tinted<br /><br />Just added this same button with 20 degree sequential tint shift.<br />More psychedelic look. <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_e_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" />)<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=856">juniper7</a> — Fri Mar 04, 2016 12:11 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
